<body>

    <div class="container">

        <h1>About Classio</h1>

        <p>
            <strong>Classio</strong> is a school management web application developed as a
            <strong>school project</strong> for the <strong>2025/2026 academic year in SoftUni BUDITEL.</strong>
        </p>

        <p>
            The project was created by <strong>Kaloyan Kirilov Boyadzhiev</strong>,
            student in <strong>class 12A</strong>.
        </p>

        <p>
            The goal of the project is to demonstrate practical knowledge in web development,
            databases, and software architecture by solving a real-world problem related to
            school organization and communication.
        </p>

        <h2>Project Purpose</h2>

        <p>
            Classio is designed to manage essential school-related information and processes,
            focusing on clarity, structure, and ease of use.
        </p>

        <ul>
            <li>Students and their academic data</li>
            <li>Teachers and assigned subjects</li>
            <li>Parents linked to students</li>
            <li>Classes, grades, and absences</li>
            <li>Role-based access and dashboards</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Technology Stack</h2>

        <div class="card">
            <p><strong>Backend</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>ASP.NET Core MVC</li>
                <li>C#</li>
                <li>Entity Framework Core</li>
                <li>ASP.NET Identity</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Database</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Microsoft SQL Server</li>
                <li>SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS)</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Frontend</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Razor Views (CSHTML)</li>
                <li>HTML5 & CSS3</li>
                <li>Custom UI styling</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>Project Structure</h2>

        <p>
            The application follows the <strong>MVC (Model-View-Controller)</strong> pattern and
            uses <strong>Areas</strong> for administrative functionality.
        </p>

        <p>
            The structure separates business logic, data access, and presentation to improve
            maintainability and readability.
        </p>

        <h2>Educational Context</h2>

        <p>
            Classio was developed for educational purposes and demonstrates:
        </p>

        <ul>
            <li>Full-stack web development concepts</li>
            <li>Database design and relationships</li>
            <li>Authentication and authorization</li>
            <li>Clean and maintainable code structure</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="footer-note">
            © 2025–2026 — Classio School Project
        </div>

    </div>

</body>
